{
  "doc_id": "11164",
  "text": "We consider agent stochastic differential model on a probability space (Ω, A, P ) with a filtration F t generated by w(t), the n-dimensional standard Wiener process ( [CITATION_1] ). Here, Ω is the sample space which consists of all outcomes for the state x at any given time t, A is the sigma algebra of all events that the state at t can be in, and P is the probability measure on the sigma algebra. The system is causal, and hence is adapted to the filtration of progressively increasing sigma algebras generated by the Wiener process",
